
[1]slander

   SLA'NDER, n.

   1. A false tale or report maliciously uttered. and tending to injure
   the reputation of another by lessening him in the esteem of his fellow
   citizens, by exposing min to impeachment and punishment, or by
   impairing his means of lining; defamation. Slander, that worst of
   poisons, ever finds an easy entrance to ignoble minds.

   2 Disgrace; reproach; disreputation; ill name.

     SLA'NDER, v.t. To defame; to injure by maliciously uttering a false
    report respecting one; to tarnish or impair the reputation of one by
                false tales, maliciously told or propagated.
